Powering Business Online: The E-Commerce Way

What is an E-commerce Business?

Global e-commerce is the new platform to discover, buy, sell, and experiment with your products and services. It caters to a wide range of audiences and helps in bridging the gap between supply and demand, which traditional markets could not achieve earlier.

The UAE market and its boom due to friendly government policies have led to a rise in low cost business setup in Dubai. Tapping the huge revenue of $3.5tn global e-commerce is much faster, easier, and more accessible now.

Why Set Up E-commerce in the UAE?

E-commerce business setup in UAE has a multiplier impact. The reasons are:

  • Region: UAE is the heart of the Middle East and the best businesses and global corporations are settled in its esteemed emirates such as Dubai, Sharjah, Abu Dhabi, Ras Al Khaimah, etc.
  • Market: 25,000 new business licenses were issued in Dubai in the first quarter of 2023. Capitalizing on market diversity and a wide range of industries made UAE the sweet spot for new entrepreneurs, founders, and C-suite executives.
  • Policies: The Government support for entrepreneurship increased new business setup in Dubai tremendously. 100% foreign ownership makes a deal-breaking statement for saving taxes and finances.

How to Set Up an E-commerce Business in the UAE?

Once your idea of business is finalized and market research is completed for demand gap knowledge, follow these 3 simple steps to open an e-commerce business in UAE:
  • Jurisdiction: Choose any of the three business zones of UAE: Freezone, Mainland, or Off-shore. Settle with the one that suits your business idea and saves input costs while serving a large market.
  • Register for Trade License: Register with the Department of Economic Development (DED) to obtain your trade license. Fees vary depending on the industry and business zone you opt for.
  • Setup Website: After you open a company in Dubai, this is the most crucial part of your e-commerce journey. Develop a user-friendly website for your customers to purchase your products and services online.

There are multiple documentation, verification, and visa requirements. To get things done within a limited time, contact the best business setup consultants in Dubai, A&A Associate.

Benefits of E-Commerce Business in the UAE

The benefits of e-commerce business in the UAE are numerous. few are highlighted below:
  • 100% Business Ownership: Your business will be completely owned by you, from end-to-end.
  • Strategic Location: Set up a Company in the UAE at strategic business locations for maximum profit and revenue generation.
  • Flexible Office Solutions: Office setup can be of your choice, customizable according to you. Though an on-site office is not necessary for e-commerce business in the UAE.
  • World Class Business Hub: Connect with like-minded entrepreneurs and founders to grow your connections and widen business opportunities.
  • Wide Range of Business Activities: Be it any industry or sector, the UAE market is ready to accept and exploit it.
  • Training Events: World-class infrastructure and business hubs for training and shaping new generations of experts.

Get Your E-Commerce License Today

A&A Associate, the master consultants and business experts of the middle east can help you get your desired e-commerce license in Dubai within 3-5 working days. We will guide you through every step of the journey and assist you in a smooth transition into the UAE market.

Get your business ideas to us and leave with a trading license today.

Ecommerce Package – AED 5,750

License Issued from SHAMS
Free Ski Dubai Passes
Inclusions
  • Physical presence not required.
  • License issued from Sharjah Media City Free Zone (SHAMS).
  • License will be issued in 3 to 5 working days.
Deliverables
  • Trade License.
  • Share Certificate or Memorandum of Association.
  • Certificate of Formation.
What can you do?
  • Any 1 media related activity.
  • Can have your own website & sell anything online
  • Can sell through any others Ecommerce platform like Noon, Amazon.
  • Eligible to have Ecommerce activity.
  • Can work anywhere in and outside UAE
Benefits
  • 100% business ownership
  • Strategic Location
  • Flexible Office Solutions
  • World Class Business Hub
  • A full range of business activity options
  • Training Events
  • Trading Platforms
Notes

This package can be availed for single shareholder.

*Conditions Apply
